Mauritius to Start Construction of Second Dam in September, l’Express Says

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-03-23T07:41:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/mauritius-to-start-construction-of-second-dam-in-september-l-express-says.html
Mauritius will start construction
of a second dam in September with a capacity of 13 million cubic
meters (43 million cubic feet) of water,  l’Express  said, citing
parliamentary answers from Utilities Minister Rashid Beebeejaun.  The 3 billion-rupee ($105 million) project, to be built
about 60 kilometers (37 miles) south of the capital,  Port-Louis ,
will be financed by  China , the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis via Johannesburg at 
1933 or  Gbell16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net  